---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About · Fablewick">
  <section class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 pt-12 pb-20 prose-story">
    <h1 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 500; font-size: 2.75rem; line-height: 1.1; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">A small light.</h1>

    <p>
      Fablewick is a free, ad-free library of stories for kids. There are stories
      already here, and there's a quiet place to make new ones — shaped to your
      reader's level.
    </p>

    <p>
      It exists because storytelling is one of the oldest ways humans have taught each
      other to be kind, brave, patient, and curious. Every story here has a small lesson
      tucked inside — never preached, never on the surface.
    </p>

    <h2 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 500; margin-top: 2.5rem;">What we don't do</h2>

    <ul>
      <li>No accounts. No sign-ups. No emails.</li>
      <li>No ads. No tracking. No cookies beyond what makes the site work.</li>
      <li>No subscriptions or paywalls.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 500; margin-top: 2.5rem;">Open source</h2>

    <p>
      The whole library is open source. The books are just folders in a public repo.
      If you write a story you'd like to share, you can contribute it. If usage grows
      enough that costs need help, we'll add a donation link — never a paywall.
    </p>

    <h2 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 500; margin-top: 2.5rem;">A note on AI</h2>

    <p>
      The "Create your own" feature uses AI to write fresh stories. AI is good, not
      perfect. Please read what it writes before reading it to a child. We've shaped
      the prompts carefully for safety and age-appropriateness, but you know your
      reader better than any algorithm.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
